member.remarks:
Subscribe in Start(), unsubscribe in OnDestroy(), and implement event method with signature
Subscribe: combatController.OnStateChanged += CharacterStateChanged;
Unsubscribe: combatController.OnStateChanged -= CharacterStateChanged;
Signature: public void CharacterStateChanged() { }

member.example:
You must include this class in order to override the standard Unity Debug class.
using Debug = ConditionalDebug;
Then you can use it exactly as if it was the standard Unity Debug class. https://docs.unity3d.com/ScriptReference/Debug.html
